.TH "rxrpc_kernel_send_data" 9 "rxrpc_kernel_send_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rxrpc_kernel_send_data \- Allow a kernel service to send data on a call
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rxrpc_kernel_send_data
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct rxrpc_call *call "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *msg "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "rxrpc_notify_end_tx_t notify_end_tx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
The socket the call is on
.IP "call" 12
The call to send data through
.IP "msg" 12
The data to send
.IP "len" 12
The amount of data to send
.IP "notify_end_tx" 12
Notification that the last packet is queued.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allow a kernel service to send data on a call.  The call must be in an state
appropriate to sending data.  No control data should be supplied in \fImsg\fP,
nor should an address be supplied.  MSG_MORE should be flagged if there's
more data to come, otherwise this data will end the transmission phase.
